title: SpaceX planning next two Falcon 9 launches in Florida
summary: The 39th and 40th launches of the year from Florida’s Space Coast are set to blast off Saturday night and Sunday night, back-to-back missions to deploy more satellites for SpaceX’s Starlink internet network.

title: Watch live: Falcon 9 test-firing imminent at Cape Canaveral
summary: SpaceX is counting down to a static fire test of a Falcon 9 rocket on pad 40 at Cape Canaveral Space Force Station in Florida. The test-firing of the booster’s nine engines is in preparation for a launch with 54 more Starlink internet satellites as soon as Sunday night.

title: Starlink Group 4-34 mission now targeting Friday after weather delays
summary: A SpaceX Falcon 9 Block 5 carrying 54 Starlink satellites is now targeted to launch at 9:27 PM EDT on Friday, Sept. 16 (01:27 UTC on Sept. 17) after unfavorable weather scrubbed attempts on Tuesday and Wednesday. This mission will be launching from Space Launch Complex 40 (SLC-40) at the Cape Canaveral Space Force Station in Florida.

title: SpaceX scrubs launch of 54 more Starlink satellites
summary: SpaceX called off a launch attempt Tuesday at Cape Canaveral due to lightning, delaying liftoff of a Falcon 9 rocket and 54 more Starlink internet satellites by 24 hours until Wednesday night.
